stic Assessment System"}],["$","div",null,{"style":{"fontSize":"1.1rem","lineHeight":"1.8","marginTop":"30px"},"children":"At Sree Jayam School (SJS), student learning is evaluated through a structured Scholastic Assessment System that measures academic progress, understanding, and overall performance throughout the academic year. The assessment system is designed according to the academic stages of learning and includes unit tests, term examinations, and periodic evaluations. The purpose of these assessments is to help students develop strong academic skills, improve their performance, and provide teachers and parents with a clear understanding of the student's progress."}]]}]}]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"row","children":[["$","div","foundation",{"className":"col-lg-6 mb-40","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"stage-card p-5","style":{"backgroundColor":"#fff","border":"1px solid #eee","borderRadius":"20px","height":"100%","boxShadow":"0 5px 25px rgba(0,0,0,0.05)"},"children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"mb-20","style":{"color":"#1A3C6E"},"children":"Foundation Stage (PS–I to Grade II)"}],["$","div",null,{"style":{"fontSize":"1rem","lineHeight":"1.7"},"children":"In the Foundation Stage, the focus is on building strong basic skills in language, numeracy, creativity, and social development. At this level, assessments are designed to be child-friendly and activity-based, encouraging students to learn through observation, participation, and simple evaluations. Teachers assess students through: Class participation, Oral assessments, Activity-based learning, Worksheets and simple evaluation. The emphasis is on concept understanding and skill development rather than formal examinations."}]]}]}],["$","div","preparatory",{"className":"col-lg-6 mb-40","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"stage-card p-5","style":{"backgroundColor":"#fff","border":"1px solid #eee","borderRadius":"20px","height":"100%","boxShadow":"0 5px 25px rgba(0,0,0,0.05)"},"children":[["$","